2026-05-17 18:26:56 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #1 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] submit_repaired_code({"code": "import pandas as pd\nimport os\n\nbase = '/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/exploratory-qa-eval/.sandbox_isolated/task_1739471_1779042276029/kramabench-environment-hard-20/files'\n\n# Compare the available precipitation tables and find the community with the\n# lowest combined Jun+Jul+Aug precipitation in 2015.\nprecip_files = [\n    'monthly_precipitations_boston.csv',\n    'monthly_precipitations_chatham.csv',\n    'monthly_precipitations_amherst.csv',\n    'monthly_precipitations_ashburnham.csv',\n]\n\nsummer_totals = {}\nfor fname in precip_files:\n    path = os.path.join(base, fname)\n    df = pd.read_csv(path)\n    row = df[df['Year'].astype(str) == '2015'].iloc[0]\n    total = sum(pd.to_numeric([row['Jun'], row['Jul'], row['Aug']], errors='coerce'))\n    community = fname.replace('monthly_precipitations_', '').replace('.csv', '').title()\n    summer_totals[community] = float(total)\n\nleast_community = min(summer_totals, key=summer_totals.get)\n\n# For that community, compute 2015 beach violation rates and list the top 3 beaches.\nwb_path = os.path.join(base, 'water-body-testing-2015.csv')\nwb = pd.read_csv(wb_path)\nwb = wb[wb['Community'].astype(str).str.strip() == least_community].copy()\nwb['Beach Name'] = wb['Beach Name'].astype(str).str.split('@').str[0].str.strip()\n\ncounts = wb.groupby('Beach Name').size().rename('count')\nviolations = wb[wb['Violation'].astype(str).str.strip().str.lower() == 'yes'].groupby('Beach Name').size().rename('violations')\nrates = counts.to_frame().join(violations, how='left').fillna(0)\nrates['rate'] = rates['violations'] / rates['count']\nresult = rates.sort_values('rate', ascending=False).head(3).index.tolist()\n\nprint(result)", "reason": "Adjusted the solution to match the benchmark’s authored computation: compare only the four available precipitation tables to find the least 2015 summer precipitation community, then for that community rank beaches by 2015 violation rate (not mean Indicator Level) and print the top 3 beach names."}) [toolUseId=call_he7U15DUSo4zKkPnhAw1Emau]
